<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/53002007/2025-26/evaluation> a ns1:EvaluationSystem ;
    ns1:evaluationDescription """In order to pass the course it is essential to
- Score at least 3.5 points (out of 10) in the final exam.
The exam may consist of the following exercises:
1) Short questions, which require the application of the theory taught. These will include, among others, closed-answer, multiple-choice questions. These are simple applications of fundamental concepts from the subject syllabus. In
In some cases they involve some simple calculation by applying an equation, or defining when an equation is applicable or what the meaning of the variables involved is.
2) Application problems or exercises, with the same characteristics as those proposed and solved during the course.

Assessment by final examination only
Students who do not wish to take the partial tests, and therefore opt for assessment by "final test only", must additionally take a final exam on all the achievement indicators. This final exam will have the same characteristics as the continuous assessment modality.

Extraordinary call
All students, both continuous assessment and final exam students, who have not passed the ordinary exam may sit the extraordinary exam, in which they will be examined for the whole course. The exam will have the same characteristics as the "final exam only"."""@es ;
